description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based with the Tissue Viability Team we are looking to recruit to the post of assistant practitioner on a 15 hr permanent contract. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and conscientious Assistant Practitioner to work with the established Tissue Viability to assist with the management of patients with a range of tissue viability issues. The applicant will be required to have experience in providing wound care to patients, implementing pressure ulcer prevention plans and have leg ulcer clinic experience. We are a dynamic, developing service and enthusiastic team providing education, advice, support and clinical care for patients across Nottingham CityCare. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be working with the tissue viability nurses based at Aspect House caring for patients across Nottingham CityCare. You will be educated and will develop specific skills in tissue viability, helping and supporting patients about their condition, you will be involved in development of your new role and support other health care professionals delivering care to patients. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need experience in caring for patients with tissue viability needs, a keen interest within the field of wound care, be able to demonstrate excellent interpersonal and communication skills.  You must be able to prioritise tasks and manage time effectively, also be able to work flexibly within the team and be confident in completing individual tasks&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The hours of work will be15 hours over 2 working days (These can be discussed and there can be some flexibility). The Service hours are 8.30am – 5pm excluding weekends and bank holidays. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Sarah Pankhurst on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sarah.pankhurst@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. on 07540670180&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
